                            <comment id="17386669" author="davsclaus" created="Sat, 24 Jul 2021 07:37:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah yeah so its because the splitter breaks down the 3 tasks into a reactive task that gets executed in parallel (you turned on parallel) but they can be executed in &quot;random&quot; order, and then each task then submit again a task for the when its done to aggregate the result, but those tasks are therefore submitted in random order, and hence why you get 231 etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So we have to move the submit ordering to an earlier phase or something&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17386670" author="davsclaus" created="Sat, 24 Jul 2021 07:41:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TODO: Added unit test in class Split123ParallelTest &lt;b&gt;DONE&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
